The paper presents a solution to the problem of understanding a system that produces a sequence of temporally ordered observations, which involves generating and interpreting a set of temporal decision rules. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), as it deals with decision-making and prediction. Additionally, the use of rule sets and experiments with both synthetic and real temporal data suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Databases (cs.DB). The paper also involves predicting the value of a decision attribute using condition attributes, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with relationships between attributes, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
